{{Quote|Isn't that the ship that wiped out Arnod's flight back in the asteroid field? The one from the Battle of Yavin?|[[Flight Lieutenant]] [[Rignik]], referring to the ''Millennium Falcon''|<ref name="DVT" />}}
'''Arnod''' served the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire's]] [[Navy/Legends|Navy]] as a [[TIE pilot]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]] fought between the Empire and the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]].<ref name="DVT" /> By [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]],<ref name="FF" /> Arnod was attached to the Imperial [[Death Squadron/Legends|Death Squadron]],<ref name="ESB" /> and led a flight<ref name="DVT" /> consisting of at least three other [[TIE/ln space superiority starfighter/Legends|TIE/LN starfighter]] [[Pilot/Legends|pilots]].<ref name="ESB" />

In 3 [[Galactic Standard Calendar|ABY]],<ref name="FF" /> the Empire participated in a victory against the Alliance at the [[Battle of Hoth/Legends|Battle of Hoth]], where the Alliance was forced to evacuate their [[Echo Base/Legends|headquarters]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Hoth/Legends|Hoth]]. Arnod's flight of [[TIE series/Legends|TIE/LN]] [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighters]] accompanied the [[Imperial II-class Star Destroyer/Legends|''Imperial II''-class Star Destroyer]] [[Avenger/Legends|''Avenger'']] in pursuing the Alliance's [[YT-1300 light freighter/Legends|YT-1300 light freighter]] [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']] through the [[Hoth system/Legends|Hoth system]] following the [[Freighter/Legends|freighter's]] escape from Hoth.<ref name="ESB" />

In their pursuit of the ''Falcon'', Arnod's flight followed the freighter as it went into the [[Hoth asteroid field/Legends|Hoth asteroid field]] in an attempt to elude the TIE/LN starfighters.<ref name="ESB" /> Arnod and the other TIE pilots were [[Death/Legends|killed]]<ref name="FF" /> when their starfighters all struck [[Asteroid/Legends|asteroids]] during the pursuit.<ref name="ESB" />

==Behind the scenes==
Arnod's starfighter was created for [[1980]]'s [[original trilogy]] film [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''Star Wars'': Episode V ''The Empire Strikes Back'']],<ref name="ESB" /> released [[May 21]] of that year.<ref name="Empire Turns 40">{{ThisWeek|6UccH037VQ0|The Empire Strikes Back Turns 40, Queen's Peril Gets a Voice, and More!|sw_url=video/the-empire-strikes-back-turns-40-queen-s-peril-gets-a-voice-and-more}}</ref> Prior to the film, the starfighter first appeared simultaneously in ''[[The Empire Strikes Back Storybook]]''<ref name="ESB storybook">''[[The Empire Strikes Back Storybook]]''</ref> and the film's [[Star Wars: The Empire Strikes Back (novelization)|novelization]],<ref name="ESB novel">[[Star Wars: The Empire Strikes Back (novelization)|''Star Wars Episode V: The Empire Strikes Back'' novelization]]</ref> both released [[April 12]] of the same year.<ref name="Amazon-RandomHouse">{{Amazon|url=Empire-Strikes-Back-Storybook/dp/0394844149|text=The Empire Strikes Back Storybook}} {{C|US hardcover}}</ref><ref name="Year by Year">''[[Star Wars Year By Year: A Visual History, New Edition]]''</ref> In [[1990]], the pilot's name was first identified in "[[Dark Voyage to Tatooine]]," a story published in [[West End Games]]' sourcebook ''[[Galaxy Guide 5: Return of the Jedi]]'' written by [[Michael Stern]].<ref name="DVT" />

